}} <br />[[V\u00edctor Mu\u00f1oz|V\u00edctor]] {{pengoal}}\n|nobars = 1\n}}\n\n----\n\n==== Semi-finals ====\n{{football box\n|date = 25 June 1986\n|time = 12:00 [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|FRA}}\n|score = [[1986 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#France vs West Germany|0\u20132]]\n|report = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3469/match=564/index.html Report]\n|team2 = {{fb|FRG}}\n|goals2 = [[Andreas Brehme|Brehme]] {{goal|9}}<br />[[Rudi V\u00f6ller|V\u00f6ller]] {{goal|89}}\n|stadium = [[Estadio Jalisco]], [[Guadalajara, Jalisco|Guadalajara]]\n|attendance = 45,000\n|referee = [[Luigi Agnolin]] ([[Italian Football Federation|Italy]])\n|nobars = 1\n}}\n\n{{football box\n| date = 25 June 1986\n| time = 16:00 [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n| team1 = {{fb-rt|ARG}}\n| score = [[1986 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Argentina vs Belgium|2\u20130]]\n| report = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3469/match=388/index.html Report]\n| team2 = {{fb|BEL}}\n| goals1 = [[Diego Maradona|Maradona]] {{goal|51||63}}\n| stadium = [[Estadio Azteca]], [[Mexico City]]\n| attendance = 114,500\n| referee = [[Antonio M\u00e1rquez Ram\u00edrez]] ([[Federaci\u00f3n Mexicana de F\u00fatbol Asociaci\u00f3n|Mexico]])\n| nobars = 1\n}}\n\n----\n\n==== Third place play-off ====\n{{football box\n|date = 28 June 1986\n|time = 12:00 [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|BEL}}\n|score = [[1986 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Third place match|2\u20134]] ([[Extra time|a.e.t.]])\n|report = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3468/match=422/index.html Report]\n|team2 = {{fb|FRA}}\n|goals1 = [[Jan Ceulemans|Ceulemans]] {{goal|11}}<br />[[Nico Claesen|Claesen]] {{goal|73}}\n|goals2 = [[Jean-Marc Ferreri|Ferreri]] {{goal|27}}<br />[[Jean-Pierre Papin|Papin]] {{goal|43}}<br />[[Bernard Genghini|Genghini]] {{goal|104}}<br />[[Manuel Amoros|Amoros]] {{goal|111|pen.}}\n|stadium = [[Estadio Cuauht\u00e9moc]], [[Puebla, Puebla|Puebla]]\n|attendance = 21,000\n|referee = [[George Courtney]] ([[The Football Association|England]])\n|nobars = 1\n}}\n\n==== Final ====\n{{Main|1986 FIFA World Cup Final}}\n{{football box\n|round=\n|date = 29 June 1986\n|time = 12:00 [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|ARG}}\n|score = [[1986 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Final|3\u20132]]\n|report = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=3467/match=393/index.html Report]\n|team2 = {{fb|FRG}}\n|goals1 = [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Brown|Brown]] {{goal|23}}<br />[[Jorge Valdano|Valdano]] {{goal|55}}<br />[[Jorge Burruchaga|Burruchaga]] {{goal|83}}\n|goals2 = [[Karl-Heinz Rummenigge|Rummenigge]] {{goal|74}}<br />[[Rudi V\u00f6ller|V\u00f6ller]] {{goal|80}}\n|stadium = [[Estadio Azteca]], [[Mexico City]]\n|attendance = 114,600\n|referee = [[Romualdo Arppi Filho]] ([[Brazilian Football Confederation|Brazil]])\n|nobars = 1\n}}\n\n== Awards ==\n<small>Source:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition=68/awards/index.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131210112952/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition%3D68/awards/index.html |archivedate=10 December 2013 |title=1986 FIFA World Cup Mexico \u2013 Awards |work=FIFA.com |publisher=[[FIFA|F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association]] |accessdate=11 March 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref></small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin: 0 auto;\"\n|-\n![[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]]\n![[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Ball|Golden Ball]]\n![[FIFA World Cup awards#Best Young Player Award|Best Young Player]]\n![[FIFA World Cup awards#FIFA Fair Play Trophy|FIFA Fair Play Trophy]]\n|-\n|align=center|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Gary Lineker]]\n|align=center|{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Diego Maradona]]\n|align=center|{{flagicon|BEL}} [[Enzo Scifo]]\n|align=center|{{fb|BRA|1968}}\n|}\n\n== Goalscorers ==\n\nGary Lineker received the [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] for scoring six goals. In total, 132 goals were scored by 82 players, with two of them credited as own goals.\n\n;6 goals<ref name=report>[https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/afdeveloping/technicaldevp/50/09/00/fwc_mexico_1986_en_part4_279.pdf FIFA World Cup \u2013 Mexico '86: Official Report], p. 228</ref>\n* {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Gary Lineker]]\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n;5 goals\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Diego Maradona]]\n* {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Careca]]\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Emilio Butrague\u00f1o]]\n{{col-3}}\n;4 goals\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Jorge Valdano]]\n* {{flagicon|DEN}} [[Preben Elkj\u00e6r Larsen]]\n* {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Alessandro Altobelli]]\n* {{flagicon|URS}} [[Igor Belanov]]\n{{col-3}}\n;3 goals\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Jan Ceulemans]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Nico Claesen]]\n* {{flagicon|DEN}} [[Jesper Olsen]]\n* {{flagicon|FRG}} [[Rudi V\u00f6ller]]\n{{col-end}}\n;2 goals\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Jorge Burruchaga]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Enzo Scifo]]\n* {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Josimar]]\n* {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[S\u00f3crates]]\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Jean-Pierre Papin]]\n{{col-3}}\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Michel Platini]]\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Yannick Stopyra]]\n* {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Fernando Quirarte]]\n* {{flagicon|MAR}} [[Abderrazak Khairi]]\n* {{flagicon|PAR|1954}} [[Roberto Caba\u00f1as]]\n{{col-3}}\n* {{flagicon|PAR|1954}} [[Julio C\u00e9sar Romero]]\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ram\u00f3n Calder\u00e9]]\n* {{flagicon|FRG}} [[Klaus Allofs]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n;1 goal\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n* {{flagicon|ALG}} [[Djamel Zidane]]\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Brown]]\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Pedro Pasculli]]\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Oscar Ruggeri]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[St\u00e9phane Demol]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Erwin Vandenbergh]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Franky Vercauteren]]\n* {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Daniel Veyt]]\n* {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Edino Nazareth Filho|Edinho]]\n* {{flagicon|BUL|1971}} [[Plamen Getov]]\n* {{flagicon|BUL|1971}} [[Nasko Sirakov]]\n* {{flagicon|DEN}} [[John Eriksen]]\n* {{flagicon|DEN}} [[Michael Laudrup]]\n* {{flagicon|DEN}} [